dismissalText.commentary: Abdul Qadir run out 1 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 100

notes: Pakistan was 2 runs away from victory in the last ball. Qadir tried an impossible 2nd run and was run out thus making India the winner. Unfortunately, the umpires had failed to notice a fielding infringement - as Kapil ran into bowl the last ball to Manzoor Elahi, only three Indian fielders were stationed in the inner ring.

milestones.description: Kapil Dev and Ravi Shastri's 112-run partnership is IND's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 97 between Gavaskar and Ravi Shastri
India's 1-run win against Pakistan is the smallest margin of victory in terms of runs in ODIs, beating 4-run win against Pakistan
